<ul>
<li>Comprehensive coverage of solid-state electronic devices</li>
<li>Clear and concise explanations of complex concepts</li>
<li>Abundant examples and problems to reinforce understanding</li>
<li>Up-to-date information on emerging technologies</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4. What is the structure of the book?</strong></p>
<p>The book is divided into 15 chapters, each covering a specific topic. The chapters follow a logical progression, starting with the basic principles of solid-state physics and progressing to more advanced topics.</p>
